Source: pdu
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), liblz4-dev, postgresql-common, zlib1g-dev
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/wublabdubdub/PDU-PostgreSQLDataUnloader

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pdu
Architecture: any
Depends: postgresql-PGVERSION, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: PostgreSQL data recovery utility for PostgreSQL PGVERSION
 PDU (PostgreSQL Data Unloader) is a standalone disaster recovery and data
 extraction utility for PostgreSQL data directories.
 .
 This package builds the version-bound PDU binary for PostgreSQL PGVERSION and
 installs it into /usr/lib/postgresql/PGVERSION/bin/pdu together with an
 example configuration file under /usr/share/postgresql/PGVERSION/pdu/.
